Abstract: Na- and Li-induced (3 fi 1) reconstruction of the Ge(111) surface was studied using a scanning tunneling microscope (STM). Despite the difference in detail, the dual-polarity images taken simultaneously for each of the Na/Ge(111)-(3 fi 1) and Li/Ge(111)-(3 fi 1) surfaces exhibited common characteristics, a lateral shift and phase reversal upon polarity reversal. We claim that those are indisputable evidences for the existance of a -bonded chain structure on the (3 fi 1) reconstruction. The analysis of the images requires a reversal of the buckling of the topmost chain atoms as compared with the most stable configurations determined by the existing theoretical calculations. PACS numbers: 61.16.Ch, 61.72.Ff, 68.35.Bs 
